The books lay piled atop each other with little in the way of rhyme or reason, as if someone was interrupted while in the process of returning them to their place.

CLINICAL NOTES:

All day, the patient has refused all offers of assistance. His abusive outbursts are offensive and intolerable! We cannot even persuade him to wash. Attempts to get food into him were violently rejected. Caring for this patient is having an adverse affect on the other patients in our ward.

This morning the patient was found huddled and screaming in a corner.
